    "body": "- docs: use \"ev\" convention in event-handlers\r\n  ```\r\n  Problem:\r\n  In autocmd examples, using \"args\" as the event-object name is vague and\r\n  may be confused with a user-command.\r\n  \r\n  Solution:\r\n  Use \"ev\" as the conventional event-object name.\r\n  ```\r\n- docs: vimfn descriptions\r\n  ```\r\n  Numerous vim funcs have very bad descriptions.\r\n  ```\r\n\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2026-03-12T10:51:35Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I think `autocmd.txt` should have some mention about `nvim_create_autocmd()` in `Defining autocommands` and `nvim_del_autocmd()` in `Removing autocommands` sections. Vim also mention `autocmd_add()` and `autocmd_delete()` in these places\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/vim/vim/blob/71fd19d7ac9e83bf63d7bad337f43cd830a5b5bd/runtime/doc/autocmd.txt#L107-L109\r\nhttps://github.com/vim/vim/blob/71fd19d7ac9e83bf63d7bad337f43cd830a5b5bd/runtime/doc/autocmd.txt#L179-L180",
